  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, org.obrel.core.Relatable

    public class AddHistoryNote
extends Interaction
    An interactive process step that adds a history note. Multiple target entities for the history records can be stored in a parameter with the type HISTORY_TARGETS. Alternatively a single history target can either be set directly in a parameter with the type HistoryRecord.TARGET or, if none of the above parameters is set, the type of the parameter containing the target must be stored in ProcessRelationTypes.HISTORY_TARGET_PARAM.

      • prepareParameters

        protected void prepareParameters()
                          throws java.lang.Exception
        This method can be overridden to prepare this step's parameters for execution. The main use of this method is for steps that are interactive to prepare the interaction parameters. This method will not be invoked if this step is re-executed because of the modification of an interactive input parameter. In that case only ProcessStep.prepareValues() will be invoked.
